9180618d-c121-422a-8bcd-3fa5b0c534ad.0eabf553-b20d-474b-9f6c-8af393a15de6.description=Purpose\:
This step gathers advanced parameters for MySQL Dump. This step has few selected parameters that can be passed as an option to 'mysqldump' command. Any additional options that are not part of the parameter list can be passed through MySQL Dump Additional Options and /or MySQL Dump Parameter File. 


Inputs\:
 command - executes MySQLGatherAdvancedParametersforBackupDump.py
 MySQL Dump Additional Options - Pipe delimited additional options for mysqldump. 
Example\: --defaults-group-suffix|abc|--ignore-table|ABC.SampleTable.
 MySQL Dump All Database - Dump all tables in all databases. Default value is True.
 MySQL Dump Compatible Output - Produce output that is more compatible with other database systems or with older MySQL servers.
 MySQL Dump Date - Include dump date as "Dump completed on" comment if --comments is given. Default value is True.
 MySQL Dump Debug Info - Print debugging information, memory, and CPU statistics when program exits.
 MySQL Dump Debug Log - Write debugging log to the given file. 
Example \: d\:t\:o,/tmp/MySQL_Sample.log.
 MySQL Dump Defaults Extra File - Read named option file in addition to usual option files.
 MySQL Dump Defaults File - Read only named option file.
 MySQL Dump Events - Dump events from dumped databases. Default value is True.
 MySQL Dump Flush logs - Flush MySQL server log files before starting dump.
 MySQL Dump Flush Privileges - Emit a FLUSH PRIVILEGES statement after dumping MySQL database.
 MySQL Dump Host - Machine Name or IP Address of the MySQL Server.
 MySQL Dump Lock All Tables - Lock all tables across all databases. Default value is True.
 MySQL Dump Log Error - Append warnings and errors to named file.
 MySQL Dump Parameter File - File containing additional parameters that needs to be passed as input to mysqldump command.
 MySQL Dump Password - Password for MySQL User.
 MySQL Dump Result File - Name of the file to store the results of the mysqldump command.
 MySQL Dump Routines - Dump stored routines (procedures and functions) from dumped databases. Default value is True.
 MySQL Dump User - MySQL User Account.
 MySQL Dump Verbose - Run the mysqldump command in verbose mode.
 host - Target to run this command against
 password - Login information for host
 username - Login information for host
 protocol - ssh/wmi
 timeout - Time (ms) before auto-exit\: use ${ExtendedTimeout} to lengthen.

Results\:
 MySQL Dump Additional Options - Pipe delimited additional options for mysqldump command.
 MySQL Dump All Database - Dump all tables in all databases.
 MySQL Dump Compatible Output - Produce output that is more compatible with other database systems or with older MySQL servers.
 MySQL Dump Date - Include dump date as "Dump completed on" in comment string.
 MySQL Dump Debug Info - Print debugging information, memory, and CPU statistics when program exits.
 MySQL Dump Debug Log - Print debugging information when the program exits.
 MySQL Dump Defaults Extra File - Read named option file in addition to usual option files.
 MySQL Dump Defaults File - Read only named option file.
 MySQL Dump Events - Dump events from dumped databases.
 MySQL Dump Flush logs - Flush MySQL server log files before starting dump.
 MySQL Dump Flush Privileges - Emit a FLUSH PRIVILEGES statement after dumping MySQL database.
 MySQL Dump Host - Machine Name or IP Address of the MySQL Server.
 MySQL Dump Lock All Tables - Lock all tables across all databases.
 MySQL Dump Log Error - Append warnings and errors to named file.
 MySQL Dump Parameter File - File containing additional parameters that needs to be passed as input to mysqldump command.
 MySQL Dump Password - Password for MySQL User.
 MySQL Dump Result File - Name of the file to store the results of the mysqldump command.
 MySQL Dump Routines - Dump stored routines from dumped databases.
 MySQL Dump User - MySQL User Account.
 MySQL Dump Verbose - Run the mysqldump command in verbose mode.
 Exit Code - Exit code of the step needed for branching.

 9180618d-c121-422a-8bcd-3fa5b0c534ad.3cc3c7bc-6470-44f4-b88a-053715763ad6.description=Purpose\:
This step gathers advanced parameters for MySQL Upgrade. This step has few selected parameters that can be passed as an option to 'mysql_upgrade' command. Any additional options that are not part of the parameter list can be passed as input through MySQL Upgrade Additional Options and /or MySQL Upgrade Parameter File parameters. 


Inputs\:
 command - executes MySQLGatherAdvancedParametersforMySQLInstanceUpgrade.py
 Clean Dump File on Failure - Specify if the dump file created as backup needs to be deleted on failure of the workflow. Default Value is False.
 Clean Dump File on Success - Specify if the dump file created as backup needs to be deleted on successful execution of the workflow. Default Value is False.
 Clean Software Binaries on Failure - Specify if the software binaries or configuration files downloaded from SA core needs to be deleted on failure of the workflow. Default Value is False.
 Clean Software Binaries on Success - Specify if the software binaries or configuration files downloaded from SA core needs to be deleted on successful execution of the workflow. Default Value is False.
 MySQL Force Upgrade - Force execution of mysql_upgrade utility, even if it has already been executed for current version of MySQL. Default value is True.
 MySQL Upgrade Additional Options - Pipe delimited additional options that can be passed as input to mysql_upgrade utility. 
Example\: --fields-enclosed-by|,|--no-autocommit|True.
 MySQL Upgrade Debug Info - Print debugging information, memory, and CPU statistics when program exits.
 MySQL Upgrade Debug Log - Write debugging log to the given file. 
Example\: d\:t\:o,/tmp/MySQL_Sample.log.
 MySQL Upgrade Defaults Extra File - Read named option file in addition to usual option files.
 MySQL Upgrade Defaults File - Read only named option file.
 MySQL Upgrade Host - Machine Name or IP Address on which the MySQL server is to be upgraded.
 MySQL Upgrade Parameter File - File containing additional parameters that needs to be passed as input to mysql_upgrade utility.
 MySQL Upgrade Password - Password of the MySQL User account that can access the MySQL server that needs to be upgraded.
 MySQL Upgrade Port - Port on which the MySQL service that needs to be upgraded is running.
 MySQL Upgrade User - User Account of the MySQL server that needs to be upgraded.
 MySQL Upgrade Verbose - Run mysql_upgrade utility in verbose mode.
 MySQL Upgrade Write Bin Log - Write all statements from mysql_upgrade utility to binary log.
 Staging Directory - Directory where the software binaries or configuration files is present/will be downloaded to from SA.
 host - Target to run this command against
 password - Login information for host
 username - Login information for host
 protocol - ssh/wmi
 timeout - Time (ms) before auto-exit\: use ${ExtendedTimeout} to lengthen.

Results\:
 Clean Dump File on Failure - Specify to delete the dump file on failure.
 Clean Dump File on Success - Specify to delete the dump file on success.
 Clean Software Binaries on Failure - Specify to delete binaries on failure.
 Clean Software Binaries on Success - Specify to delete binaries on success.
 MySQL Force Upgrade - Force execution of mysql_upgrade utility.
 MySQL Upgrade Additional Options - Pipe delimited additional options for mysql_upgrade utility.
 MySQL Upgrade Debug Info - Print debugging information when program exits.
 MySQL Upgrade Debug Log - Write debugging log to the given file.
 MySQL Upgrade Defaults Extra File - Read named option file in addition to usual option files.
 MySQL Upgrade Defaults File - Read only named option file.
 MySQL Upgrade Host - Host name or IP address on which the MySQL server is to be upgraded.
 MySQL Upgrade Parameter File - File containing additional parameters that needs to be passed as input to mysql_upgrade utility.
 MySQL Upgrade Password - Password of the MySQL User account.
 MySQL Upgrade Port - Port on which the MySQL is running.
 MySQL Upgrade User - User Account of the MySQL server.
 MySQL Upgrade Verbose - Run mysql_upgrade utility in verbose mode.
 MySQL Upgrade Write Bin Log - Write all statements to binary log.
 Staging Directory - Directory containing the software binaries or configuration files.
 Exit Code - Exit code of the step needed for branching.

1. Value given as input in the Parameter List
2. Value given as part of MySQL Dump Additional Options
3. Value given as MySQL Dump Parameter File

 9180618d-c121-422a-8bcd-3fa5b0c534ad.description=<pre>
 Usage instructions

This workflow upgrades the MySQL Instance. The existing instance is taken as a backup and is stored in the location specified by the user. In-place RPM upgrade is performed if the upgrades are minor. The existing version is removed and a new installation is done for any major upgrades. After the RPM upgrade, upgrading the databases and the table is performed by running the mysql_upgrade utility.


 Dependencies

\# Root user privilege is required to install or upgrade the RPM.
\# MySQL client must be installed on the server, as the workflow uses mysql_upgrade utility which in turn uses mysqlcheck utility. The mysqlcheck utility is part of MySQL client RPM.



 Results verification

Execute the mysql -u root -e 'Select Version()' command on the shell to verify that the version displayed is the updated version to which MySQL was to be upgraded.

 Notification plan

None
 Required Inputs

 Server Target - The desired target to run this flow against.
 Server Target Username - The user to login to the Server Target as.
 Server Target Password - The password to login as the Server Target Username.
 Download Source Host - The target host where the files needed for this flow can be downloaded from.
 Download Source Path - The path to where the files can be found on the Download Source Host.
 MySQL Backup Dump Location - Location to store the dump of databases for backup purpose.
 Server.Become Routine - No description
 Software Binaries - Comma separated list of RPMs which needs to be installed.

 Optional Inputs

 Clean Code Base - Remove code base from target after execution (True || False).
 Clean JRE - Remove JRE from target after execution (True || False).
 Download From SA - Download binaries from SA (True || False). Must set override for 'SAUser' System Account.
 SA Folder Path - Location of binaries on SA. Must set override for 'SAUser' System Account.
 Debug Level - Set level of output [(least) 1-5 (most)]
 MySQL Upgrade Write Bin Log - Write all statements from mysql_upgrade utility to binary log.
 MySQL Dump User - MySQL User Account.
 MySQL Upgrade Password - Password of the MySQL User account that can access the MySQL server that needs to be upgraded.
 MySQL Force Upgrade - Force execution of mysql_upgrade utility, even if it has already been executed for current version of MySQL. Default value is True.
 MySQL Dump Flush logs - Flush MySQL server log files before starting dump.
 MySQL Dump Events - Dump events from dumped databases. Default value is True.
 MySQL Dump Debug Info - Print debugging information, memory, and CPU statistics when program exits.
 MySQL Dump Compatible Output - Produce output that is more compatible with other database systems or with older MySQL servers.
 MySQL Upgrade Debug Log - Write debugging log to the given file. 
Example\: d\:t\:o,/tmp/MySQL_Sample.log.
 MySQL Dump Debug Log - Write debugging log to the given file. 
Example \: d\:t\:o,/tmp/MySQL_Sample.log.
 MySQL Dump Verbose - Run the mysqldump command in verbose mode.
 MySQL Dump Parameter File - File containing additional parameters that needs to be passed as input to mysqldump command.
 Clean Software Binaries on Success - Specify if the software binaries or configuration files downloaded from SA core needs to be deleted on successful execution of the workflow. Default Value is False.
 MySQL Upgrade Verbose - Run mysql_upgrade utility in verbose mode.
 MySQL Dump Additional Options - Pipe delimited additional options for mysqldump. 
Example\: --defaults-group-suffix|abc|--ignore-table|ABC.SampleTable.
 MySQL Dump Log Error - Append warnings and errors to named file.
 Staging Directory - Directory where the software binaries or configuration files is present/will be downloaded to from SA.
 MySQL Upgrade Additional Options - Pipe delimited additional options that can be passed as input to mysql_upgrade utility. 
Example\: --fields-enclosed-by|,|--no-autocommit|True.
 MySQL Dump Defaults Extra File - Read named option file in addition to usual option files.
 MySQL Upgrade Defaults Extra File - Read named option file in addition to usual option files.
 MySQL Dump Password - Password for MySQL User.
 MySQL Upgrade User - User Account of the MySQL server that needs to be upgraded.
 MySQL Dump Flush Privileges - Emit a FLUSH PRIVILEGES statement after dumping MySQL database.
 Clean Software Binaries on Failure - Specify if the software binaries or configuration files downloaded from SA core needs to be deleted on failure of the workflow. Default Value is False.
 MySQL Upgrade Debug Info - Print debugging information, memory, and CPU statistics when program exits.
 MySQL Dump Defaults File - Read only named option file.
 MySQL Dump Date - Include dump date as "Dump completed on" comment if --comments is given. Default value is True.
 MySQL Dump Result File - Name of the file to store the results of the mysqldump command.
 MySQL Upgrade Defaults File - Read only named option file.
 MySQL Dump Routines - Dump stored routines (procedures and functions) from dumped databases. Default value is True.
 MySQL Dump All Database - Dump all tables in all databases. Default value is True.
 Clean Dump File on Success - Specify if the dump file created as backup needs to be deleted on successful execution of the workflow. Default Value is False.
 MySQL Upgrade Port - Port on which the MySQL service that needs to be upgraded is running.
 MySQL Dump Lock All Tables - Lock all tables across all databases. Default value is True.
 Clean Dump File on Failure - Specify if the dump file created as backup needs to be deleted on failure of the workflow. Default Value is False.
 MySQL Dump Host - Machine Name or IP Address of the MySQL Server.
 MySQL Upgrade Host - Machine Name or IP Address on which the MySQL server is to be upgraded.
 MySQL Upgrade Parameter File - File containing additional parameters that needs to be passed as input to mysql_upgrade utility.
